  <h1>
   vertex_delete_buffer
  </h1>
  This function can be used to remove a previously created vertex buffer (see
  <a href="vertex_create_buffer.htm">
   <span>
    vertex_create_buffer()
   </span>
  </a>
  ) from system memory. This will also remove all vertex data for any custom primitives that it contained.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">vertex_delete_buffer(buffer);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      buffer
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Primitives/vertex_create_buffer.htm">
        Vertex Buffer ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The vertex buffer to be removed.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">vertex_delete_buffer(v_buff);
</code></pre>
  The above code will delete from memory the buffer indexed in the variable "v_buff".
 </body>
